Spanish: <s>El danés hizo su debut en el partido de 1997 en Valderrama, donde un bando capitaneado por Seve Ballesteros mantenía una ventaja de cinco puntos sobre los americanos, pero al final solo lograron acabar con los otros pisándoles los talones por un margen mínimo, ganando 14½-13½.</s>
English: <s>The Danes made their debut in the 1997 Ryder Cup at Valderrama, where a team captained by Seve Ballesteros held a five-point lead over the Americans, but in the end only managed to finish with the other team on their heels by a minimum margin, winning 14½-13½.</s>
The 1997 Ryder Cup was held at Valderrama Golf Club in Sotogrande, Spain, from September 19 to 21, 1997. The United States team, captained by Ben Crenshaw, defeated the European team, captained by Seve Ballesteros, by a score of 14½-13½.
The 1997 Ryder Cup was the 23rd edition of the Ryder Cup, a biennial match play competition between teams from Europe and the United States. It was held at Valderrama Golf Club in Sotogrande, Spain, from September 19 to 21, 1997. The United States team, captained by Ben Crenshaw, defeated the European team, captained by Seve Ballesteros, by a score of 14½-13½.

--------------------
Spanish: <s>"No paras de recordarte que hicimos un gran torneo en Valderrama; también lo hicimos en Brookline y perdimos, lo hicimos en Valderrama y ganamos, pero por muy poco", dijo Bjorn, retratado, después de ver a la generación de 2018 ganar 5-3 el viernes y ayer liderarlo con un 10-6 en Le Golf National.</s>

Transient ischemic attack (TIA) is also known as a "mini-stroke" or "warning stroke." A TIA is a stroke-like episode that lasts only a few minutes to a few hours. During a TIA, blood flow to a part of the brain is temporarily blocked, causing symptoms similar to those of a stroke.
